The paper deals with user association in a heterogeneous network (HetNet) with massive MIMO and small cells. This involves optimization algorithms for resource allocation and user association, which are typical topics in the areas of network information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses game theory models for distributed user association, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MM) and game theory (cs.GT). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.NI and cs.IT, followed by cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.GT.
